    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Low-Dose Radiation Research Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Energy to carry out a research program&nbsp;on low-dose radiation to enhance the scientific understanding of the effects of exposure and to improve risk-assessment and risk-management methods. </p> <p>"Low-dose radiation" is defined as a dose less than 100 millisieverts. (The Nuclear Regulatory Commission limits an adult's annual occupational radiation dose to 50 millisieverts.)</p>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2017-12-18</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-06-18T22:25:45Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <updateDate>2017-12-18T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Low-Dose Radiation Research Act of 2018</strong></p> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill requires the Department of Energy to carry out a research program&nbsp;on low-dose radiation to enhance the scientific understanding of the effects of exposure and to improve risk-assessment and risk-management methods. </p> <p>"Low-dose radiation" is defined as a dose less than 100 millisieverts. (The Nuclear Regulatory Commission limits an adult's annual occupational radiation dose to 50 millisieverts.)</p>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2018-02-13</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Passed House amended</actionDesc>
